Stuart J. Yarbrough CPAGeneral Partner, Crosshill Georgetown Capital, L.PAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 5 different industries.See Board Relationships66--
Background

		Mr. Stuart J. Yarbrough, CPA serves as a General Partner of Crosshill Georgetown Capital, L.P and CrossHill Debt II, L.P. Mr. Yarbrough served as the Chief Executive Officer of 3Point Capital Partners, LLC since February 2007 and served as its Managing Partner. Mr. Yarbrough co-founded CrossHill Financial Group, Inc. in 1994 and served as its Managing Director since April 1994 and it's Principal from April 1994 to February 2007. He has 22 years of experience with venture ... capital, investment banking and public accounting. Mr. Yarbrough experience includes advising clients in the negotiation of mergers and acquisitions, including due diligence, loan restructuring and refinancing and capital raising options and strategies and strategic planning. From 1985 to 1994, he served as Managing Partner of the Washington DC office of BDO Seidman. He started his career in public accounting with Ernst & Young. Mr. Yarbrough founded Adams & Yarbrough, an accounting and consulting firm that specialized in providing services to the banking and thrift industries. He served as Chairman of Incumaker, Inc. since September 2, 2005 and has been its Director since September 2, 2005. Mr. Yarbrough is the Director of Opus Global Holdings. He serves as a Director of Fundtech Ltd. Mr. Yarbrough has been a Director of Fundtech Holdings, LLC since May 16, 2007 and has been its Lead Independent Director since October 4, 2008. He has been the Chairman and a Director at Scientigo Inc. (Formerly Market Central Inc) since September 6, 2005. He has been a Director of BAE Systems IT, Inc. since March 2003. Mr. Yarbrough serves as a Director at DigtialNet Holdings Inc., SBR, Inc., and IQNavigator, Inc. He serves as a Member of Board of Advisors at CrossHill Financial Group, Inc. Mr. Yarbrough served as a Director of Solera Holdings Inc. from May 16, 2007 to March 3, 2016 and as its Lead Independent Director from October 4, 2008 to March 4, 2016. He served as a Director of Riggs National Corporation since January 27, 2005 and served as a Director of Riggs Bank NA since December 2004. Mr. Yarbrough served as a Director of DigitalNet Holdings Inc., since March 2003. He has been a Director of Incumaker, Inc. since September 02, 2005. He is a Member of the Economic Club of Washington and a member of Leadership Washington. Mr. Yarbrough was named to the Atlantic Coast Conference Honor Roll for outstanding academic and athletic achievement. He has 35 years of experience with venture capital, investment banking and public accounting. Mr. Yarbrough is a Certified Public Accountant and holds a B.A. degree in Management Science and Accounting from Duke University in 1972.Read Full Background




