Our Partners 
Stuart J. Yarbrough – Managing Partner
  Stuart J. Yarbrough has thirty years experience with venture capital, investment banking and public accounting.  Prior to becoming the managing partner of 3Point, Mr. Yarbrough served as a principal of CrossHill Financial Group, a venture capital firm which he co-founded.  He began his career with Ernst & Young and after five years, he founded Adams & Yarbrough, an accounting and consulting firm that specialized in providing services to the banking and thrift industries.  In 1985, BDO Seidman acquired Adams & Yarbrough and brought Mr. Yarbrough on board as its Managing Partner in the D.C. Office and elected him to its U.S. Board of Directors.  Mr. Yarbrough recently served on the Board of Directors of DigitalNet Holdings, Inc. prior to its acquisition by BAE Systems North America, Inc. Mr. Yarbrough recently served on the Board of Directors of Riggs National Corporation and Riggs Bank, N.A. prior to its acquisition by PNC Financial Services Group, and on the Board of Directors of SBR, Inc., a leading manufacturer of various building products, prior to its acquisition by Fortune Brands, Inc. Mr. Yarbrough is a CPA and previously an NASD registered principal.  Mr. Yarbrough holds a BA in Management Sciences – Accounting, from Duke University where he was named to the Atlantic Coast Conference Honor Roll for outstanding academic and athletic achievement.
 

 


 
 
 








