Join Our Team

One of the fastest growing risk and compliance companies in the world. The most recognized companies as customers. The world's pre-eminent private equity company behind us. And really smart, fun, resourceful people as colleagues... Opus is a great place to work.


View Job Openings











Ben Gould
Managing Director, EMEA and APAC



 







Ben leads all commercial and strategic activity for Opus across EMEA and APAC from their European headquarters in London.
Having started his career in business development, Ben has spoken extensively to senior compliance, data and technology executives across a wide-range of organisations and industries. This deep understanding of the challenges they face in effectively addressing their regulatory obligations, allows Ben to support Opus clients in achieving their aspirations, specifically related to Compliance, Reference Data and Third Party Management.
Ben is a veteran of the data and technology business, and has held prior positions with Datamonitor, ICC and Equifax.












Kelvin Dickenson
Vice President, Compliance and Entity Data



 










Kelvin is responsible for leading a Customer focused product roadmap to ensure KYC/AML and vendor/third party due diligence compliance with a range of regulatory requirements. Prior to joining Opus in 2014, Kelvin was at Dun & Bradstreet for 9 years. most recently as Managing Director of Compliance Solutions and previously as principal consultant for several of D&B’s strategic Customers, leading engagements in Compliance, reference data, credit review and risk management.
Before joining D&B, Kelvin spent a combined 20 years in Compliance, Credit, Loss Prevention and Managerial roles at two major financial institutions where his responsibilities included developing CIP policies, procedures, data sources and technology solutions to meet the requirements of the USA Patriot Act. Kelvin is a member of the charter class of Certified Financial Crime Specialists and is a current member of the advisory board at the Association of Certified Financial Crimes Specialists.











Sandeep Bhide
Vice President, 3PM Product Strategy



 







Sandeep has spent more than two decades in the software industry building traditional and cloud-based enterprise software solutions, bringing them to market, and supporting them over multiple release cycles.
Prior to Hiperos, Sandeep spent over eight years at Vistaar Technologies during two tenures. Most recently, he ran the technology services group of Vistaar’s healthcare subsidiary. His responsibilities included the development, pre-sales support and delivery of an enterprise-class patient-flow and throughput-management solution for some of the largest healthcare providers. Previously, Sandeep was the head of technical services at Heartbeat Software, where he engineered the turnaround of performance and service levels of a 65-person engineering and support team, orchestrating the transition of the development center from Bangkok, Thailand to Pune, India.
Sandeep holds a bachelor’s degree in computer engineering from Pune University and an MBA in finance from Rutgers University.











Rich Wilkie
Senior Vice President, Engineering



 







Rich has over twenty years of experience delivering traditional and cloud-based products and services. He is currently responsible for Opus’s development and operations efforts across all product lines.
Prior to joining Opus, Rich held executive IT management roles at several Fortune 500 companies including Hewlett-Packard, Nortel Networks, Apollo Education Group, and ECI Telecom. In these roles, he was responsible for building and supporting numerous enterprise, carrier and consumer products to the financial services, telecom, education, and medical instruments industries.
Rich holds a BS in Electrical Engineering from the University of Massachusetts and resides in Pittsburgh, PA.











Doug Udoff
Senior Vice President, Customer Success



 







Doug has spent his entire 25-plus year career in the software industry – helping customers maximize the value they receive in their technology investments. Doug is responsible for all aspects of customer success, including implementation, customer support and long-term customer success. He was Senior Vice President of Customer Success at Hiperos prior to the Opus acquisition.
Prior to joining Hiperos in 2009, Doug was vice president of services at Misys, a UK-based software company. While at Misys, Doug oversaw a team of 550 consultants that produced $125 million in annual revenue. Prior to Misys, Doug spent more than 10 years at Oracle during two tenures. He was group vice president responsible for the North American consulting supply organization, and he played an integral part in integrating PeopleSoft’s consulting business with Oracle’s. In between his tenures, Doug joined Ariba to start the Eastern Region services team. Doug eventually became vice president of North American services, overseeing an important profit center for the company.
Doug holds a bachelor of arts degree in computer and informational sciences from the University of Delaware.











Ajit Tharaken
Senior Vice President, Operations



 


Ajit is responsible for the day-to-day operations of Opus products sold and delivered in Europe and Asia.
Prior to the Opus acquisition, Ajit led the teams that develop Alacra’s innovative professional products portfolio and supervised all client engagements. In this role, he oversaw the design, creation and development of Alacra’s professional products with a large emphasis on customer relations.
Prior to joining Alacra in 1999, Ajit was the Director of Technology at a fund of funds where he created an internet based hedge fund application now owned by Morningstar.
He has a Master’s Degree in Computer Science from Columbia University in the City of New York.











Lee Kirschbaum
Senior Vice President, Product, Marketing, and Alliances



 







Lee is responsible for leading Opus product strategy and management, alliances and global marketing including branding, corporate communications, customer programs and events. Before joining Opus, Lee was President of the Compliance Division at Kroll, a leading global provider of investigations, compliance, due diligence, cyber security, and e-discovery solutions. Prior to holding this role, Lee served as senior vice president of operations where he was responsible for Kroll’s business operations, shared services, marketing, strategy, and business development. He joined the company in January 2011, initially serving as a vice president and head of strategy for Altegrity.
Prior to joining Kroll, Lee served for eight years at Dun & Bradstreet in a number of senior leadership roles. Earlier in his career, he helped start the internal corporate strategy group at Qwest Communications and was a consultant in strategy practice at Cap Gemini Ernst & Young. Lee graduated with honors from the University of Chicago and earned his master’s of business administration degree from Columbia Business School, where he graduated with Beta Gamma Sigma honors.











Mark DeLuca
Senior Vice President, Worldwide Sales



 







Mark has spent over two decades in the enterprise software market. At Opus, Mark is responsible for driving revenue growth and building a world-class sales organization. Mark was Senior Vice President of Sales at Hiperos prior to the company’s Opus acquisition.
Prior to Hiperos, Mark built and ran the Eastern Region sales team at Aravo, a supplier information management software company. At Aravo, Mark’s team increased the company-wide subscription revenue by over 75%. Prior to Aravo, Mark was a senior manager in Accenture’s business process outsourcing sales organization. Before joining Accenture, Mark spent seven years at Ariba, where he was consistently one of the top-producing account executives. Prior to Ariba, Mark was at PeopleSoft. Mark’s sales career started at ADP where, during his 12-year tenure, he made President’s Club every quota-carrying year.
Mark holds a bachelor’s degree in business administration and English from Rutgers University.











Mike Angle
Chief Technology Officer



 







Mike was Co-founder, President and Chief Operating Officer of Alacra before the company’s Opus acquisition. Prior to Alacra, Mike was Vice President of Technology at Technimetrics, Inc., a $20 million financial information company. His responsibilities included managing all aspects of technical development and operations.
Previously, Mike spent three years as a Product Development Manager for EJV Partners, where his responsibilities included product definition, technical implementation and support of Communications and Real-Time Products.
He holds a BS in Computer Science from Rensselaer Polytechnic Institute. He resides in Warwick, NY.











Janet Coddington
Chief Financial Officer



 







Janet is an established corporate finance executive with extensive hands-on experience building, strengthening, and leading the corporate finance function for private companies in various start-up and high growth situations. She was CFO of Hiperos prior to the company’s Opus acquisition. She is focused on helping Opus enhance operations, expand its high-profile customer base, and maximize profits.
Prior to joining Hiperos, Janet was the CFO of SANpulse Technologies, a leading organization delivering advanced SAN optimization products and services. During her employment, she reduced the expense burn by 50% and maintained effective relationships with the key stakeholders. Before SANpulse, Janet spent a decade at Lumeta Corporation, where she held the positions of Chief Financial Officer and VP of Finance. During her tenure at Lumeta, she played a key role in evaluating mergers and acquisitions, raised millions of dollars in venture capital, and developed compensation and benefits packages to attract best-in-breed talent. Prior to Lumeta, Janet was employed at Telelogic North America as the Vice President of Finance, and as Controller at Quality Systems & Software, Inc.
Janet holds a Bachelor of Science in Business Management, Finance from East Stroudsburg University. She also is a member of the Institute of Management Accountants (IMA), New Jersey Technical Council (NJTC) and Society for Human Resources Management (SHRM).











Stuart J. Yarbrough
Director



 


Stuart J. Yarbrough has a unique background that is a combination of thirty five years experience with venture capital, investment banking and public accounting. Prior to its final distributions, he served as the CEO of 3Point Capital Partners, a private equity firm, which focused on the building products and outdoor lifestyle sectors. Previously, he was a principal at CrossHill Financial Group, a venture debt firm he co-founded which provided senior secured debt financings to growth companies. Prior to establishing the debt funds, Mr. Yarbrough’s responsibilities included representing growth companies in investment banking transactions, closing ‘merger and sell’ transactions with total value in excess of $1.5 B and placing capital in excess of $1B.
Prior to co-founding CrossHill Financial Group in 1994, Mr. Yarbrough spent the previous twenty-two years in public accounting. He began his career with Ernst & Young and after five years, he founded Adams & Yarbrough, an accounting and consulting firm that specialized in providing services to the banking and thrift industries. In 1985, BDO Seidman acquired Adams & Yarbrough. BDO Seidman, a leading international accounting and consulting firm, brought Mr. Yarbrough on board as its Managing Partner in the DC Office and elected him to its U.S. Board of Directors.
In addition to serving on the Board of Directors of Opus, Mr. Yarbrough currently serves on the Board of Directors and as Chairman of the Audit Committee of Assured Partners, Inc., a national property and casualty and employee benefits brokerage firm, and Optimal Blue, LLC, a provider of the mortgage industry’s digital marketplace connecting lenders, investors and providers.
Mr. Yarbrough is a CPA and previously held Professional Securities Licenses as a General Securities Principal (Series 24), General Securities Representative (Series 7), and Uniform Securities Agent State Law (Series 63). Mr. Yarbrough attended Duke University on a basketball scholarship. He graduated in 1972 with a BA in Management Sciences – Accounting. He was named to the Atlantic Coast Conference Honor Roll for achieving outstanding academic and athletic achievement.











Aaron D. Cohen
 Managing Director, GTCR



 


Aaron joined GTCR in 2003 and is currently a managing director of the firm. He previously worked at Hicks, Muse, Tate & Furst and in the Mergers & Acquisitions group of Salomon Smith Barney. He holds a BS in accountancy with High Honors from the University of Illinois at Urbana–Champaign.
Aaron currently is a director of Callcredit Information Group, Ironshore, and Opus. In addition, Aaron was previously a director of past successful investments AssuredPartners, Fundtech, Premium Credit Limited and Protection 1 and played an instrumental role in GTCR’s investments in Prestige Brands.
Aaron is active in the community and serves on the board of Chicago Youth Programs. Chicago Youth Programs improves the life opportunities and health of at-risk children by offering tutoring, healthcare, recreational activities and career placement services that promote whole-child development.











Collin E. Roche
Managing Director, GTCR



 


Collin joined GTCR in 1996 and is currently a managing director of the firm. Previously, Collin was an associate at EVEREN Securities in Chicago and an analyst with Goldman, Sachs & Company in New York. He holds an MBA from Harvard Business School and a BA in political economy from Williams College.
Collin is co-head of the Financial Services & Technology group at GTCR. Currently, he is a director of Aligned Asset Managers/The Townsend Group, Callcredit Information Group, ConvergEx, and Opus. Collin was previously a director of GTCR investments including Cambridge Protection, Fundtech, HSM Electronic Services, National Processing Company, Premium Credit Limited, PrivateBancorp, Protection 1, Skylight Financial, Syniverse, Transaction Network Services, TransFirst and VeriFone.
Outside of work, Collin stays involved in the community as a member of the board of directors of the Lyric Opera of Chicago and with various charitable institutions. In addition, Collin is active in supporting the educational missions of Harvard Business School and Williams College.











Steven Goldstein
Vice Chairman



 











Steve Goldstein is the Vice Chairman of Opus, the rapidly growing regulatory technology company where he is responsible for product and marketing strategy. Prior to his role at Opus, Steve was the co-founder, Chairman and CEO of Alacra, Inc., which was acquired by Opus in September 2015. Steve has been working in financial technology for over 30 years. He served on the New York Federal Reserve’s Small Business Advisory Council from 2009-2012 and also served on the Private Sector Advisory Group for the global legal entity identification (LEI) initiative. He has been a speaker, panelist and moderator at numerous industry conferences covering business information, regulatory technology, reference data and compliance. Steve has a bachelor’s degree in Marketing from SUNY Albany and an MBA in Finance from the Johnson Graduate School of Business at Cornell University.












Julio Quinteros
Senior Vice President, Strategy and Business Development



 










Julio is responsible for strategy and business development. He is a 17-year Wall Street equity research veteran and spent the last 15-years at global investment bank Goldman, Sachs & Co.
As a senior equity analyst, he led the IT Services research effort at Goldman Sachs where his coverage included a diverse set of enterprise facing companies including consulting, outsourcing, and offshore models. In financial technologies, Julio focused on point-of-sale technologies, acquirers, prepaid, payroll, information services, and other payment processors.
During his tenure at Goldman, Julio ranked as the top stock Internet and Computer Services stock picker in the 2006 Wall Street Journal Annual Analyst Ranking survey and placed among the top stock pickers in his sector in 2009 and 2012.
Prior to Goldman, he worked at Credit Suisse as a member of the Electronic Banking and IT Services team. He also worked at Electronic Data Systems as part of the Financial Industry Group in a market analysis and strategic planning capacity.
Julio holds a Bachelor of Arts degree in International Relations from the University of Southern California.











Emanuele “Manny” Conti
CEO & Director



 







Manny is the Chief Executive Officer and Director of Opus, which currently includes the Alacra and Hiperos product lines. He brings more than 25 years of leadership experience at companies across a diverse range of industries. He has extensive experience in the risk management and data analytics industry with a proven track record of building growth-oriented businesses around the world.
He most recently was the CEO of Kroll Inc., a leading global provider of risk management solutions which included investigations, compliance, cyber security, eDiscovery and data management. Prior to Kroll, Manny was a senior executive with Dun & Bradstreet including roles as President of North America and International. Before Dun & Bradstreet, he led the Corporate Strategy team for Qwest Communications. He also held leadership positions at Viant, an e-commerce consulting firm, and Ernst & Young LLP, where he was a founding member of the firm’s strategy practice. Earlier in his career, he held various positions with General Motors.
Mr. Conti earned a Bachelor of Science degree in Finance at Bowling Green State University and an MBA at the University of Chicago.











Doug Bergeron
Founder & Executive Chairman



 







Doug Bergeron is the founder and Executive Chairman of Opus. He is a 23-year financial technology industry veteran. In 2001, he led the acquisition of VeriFone from Hewlett-Packard in a transaction valued at $50M. In 2002, GTCR partnered with Doug and embarked upon a strategy to aggressively grow VeriFone into a multi-national company that would have an enterprise value exceeding $4 billion by 2013.
From 2002 through 2012, VeriFone’s revenue grew from $297 million to nearly $1.9 billion as a result of an aggressively executed international expansion strategy and a number of key acquisitions. In 2005, VeriFone IPO’d and became listed on the New York Stock Exchange under the symbol “PAY”. Today, VeriFone is active in over 100 countries worldwide and employs nearly 5,000 people.
From 1990 through 1999, Doug served in a number of executive management positions at SunGard Data Systems, including Managing Director of SunGard Capital Markets N.A., President of SunGard Futures Systems, and Group CEO of SunGard Brokerage Systems Group.
Doug holds an Honours Bachelor of Arts in Computer Science from York University in Toronto and a Masters of Science in Systems Management from the University of Southern California in Los Angeles. In 2013, he was awarded an Honorary Doctorate of Laws (LLD) from York University.
Doug is a permanent member of the Council on Foreign Relations, a five-time delegate to the World Economic Forum in Davos, Switzerland, and has been a frequent guest on CNBC and Fox Business. He is married to Sandra and is the father of five children.















